98c \ub2ec\ub77c\uc9c0\ub294 \ud504\ub85c\uc57c\uad6c]. Sportsseoul.com. Retrieved on 2011-04-02.</ref><ref>[http://osen.mt.co.kr/news/view.html?gid=G1005140067 \u00c7\u0143\u0105\u0161 \u0102\u00d6\u00b0\u00ed\u0154\u00c7 \u02dd\u015f\u0106\u00f7\u0102\u00f7 \u017c\u0141\u0139\u00cd\u0139\u00d7\u0154\u00ce\u00b8\u0150\u0106\u017d \u0154\u00fc\u0161\u017d \u0161\u011a\u013e\u0111\u017e\u00ee OSEN]. Osen.mt.co.kr. Retrieved on 2011-04-02.</ref><ref>[http://osen.co.kr/news/Sports_View.asp?gisano=G1004020122 ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722134615/http://osen.co.kr/news/Sports_View.asp?gisano=G1004020122 |date=July 22, 2011 }}</ref> It is one of two major baseball governing bodies; the other is the [[Korea Baseball Association]] ({{lang-ko|\ub300\ud55c\uc57c\uad6c\ud611\ud68c}}), which is the governing body for [[Amateur sports|amateur]] baseball competitions.<ref>http://www.baseball.coachesvideolibrary.com/news.php?action=view&news_id=201</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/include/print.asp?newsIdx=8222 |title=News Article |publisher= |date= |accessdate=2011-10-15}}</ref><ref>[http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/opinon/2010/05/266_41922.html Korea and Baseball]. Koreatimes.co.kr (2009-03-25). Retrieved on 2011-04-02.</ref><ref>[http://www.cbs.co.kr/nocut/Show.asp?IDX=1470341 \uc544\ub9c8 \uc57c\uad6c\ub300\ud68c\uc5d0 \ud504\ub85c\uc2ec\ud310\ub3c4 \ucd9c\uc7a5 \uac00\ub2a5 - \ub178\ucef7\ub274\uc2a4]. Cbs.co.kr. Retrieved on 2011-04-02.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://osen.co.kr/news/Sports_View.asp?gisano=G1005110044 |accessdate=May 24, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722145131/http://osen.co.kr/news/Sports_View.asp?gisano=G1005110044 |archivedate=July 22, 2011 }}</ref>\n\nThe KBO is a member of the [[International Baseball Federation]] (IBAF), and is responsible for the [[South Korea national baseball team|national baseball team]] for the [[World Baseball Classic]] and [[Asia Series]].<ref>Schwarz, Alan. (2009-03-20) [https://www.nytimes.com/2009/03/21/sports/baseball/21wbcjapan.html Japan Defeats Korea, Setting Semifinal Games]. NYTimes.com. Retrieved on 2011-04-02.</ref><ref>[http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/sports/2009/11/136_3695.html National Team Full of Aging Stars]. Koreatimes.co.kr (2007-05-28). Retrieved on 2011-04-02.</ref> National team participation in other competitions is governed by the Korea Baseball Association.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.olympicbaseball.com/2008/03/05/korea-release-24-man-olympic-qualifier-roster |title=Korea release 24-man Olympic Qualifier Roster &#124; Olympic Baseball Blog |publisher=Olympicbaseball.com |date=2008-03-05 |accessdate=2011-10-15}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n:''See footnote''<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/bullpen/Category:Korea_Baseball_Organization_Awards Category:Korea Baseball Organization Awards]. Baseball-Reference.com (Sports Reference LLC). Retrieved 2010-07-02.</ref> ''and [[Baseball awards#South Korea]]''\n\n*[[KBO League Most Valuable Player Award|KBO League MVP Award]]<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/bullpen/Korea_Baseball_Organization_Most_Valuable_Player_Award KBO Most Valuable Player Award]. Baseball-Reference.com (Sports Reference LLC). Retrieved 2010-07-02. ''See also'': [[List of CPBL MVP of the Year Award|Chinese Professional Baseball League MVP of the Year Award]] and [[Nippon Professional Baseball Most Valuable Player Award]].</ref>\n*KBO League Rookie of the Year Award<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/bullpen/Korea_Baseball_Organization_Rookie_of_the_Year KBO Rookie of the Year]. Baseball-Reference.com (Sports Reference LLC). Retrieved 2010-07-02. ''See also'': [[CPBL Rookie of the Year Award|Chinese Professional Baseball League Rookie of the Year Award]] and [[Nippon Professional Baseball Rookie of the Year Award]].</ref>\n*[[KBO League Golden Glove Award]]<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/bullpen/Korea_Baseball_Organization_Gold_Glove