ie=y|OLB|IR}}\n{{NFLplayer|59|Antonio Coleman|rookie=y|OLB|IR}}\n{{NFLplayer|54|Andra Davis|ILB|IR}}\n{{NFLplayer|81|Marcus Easley|rookie=y|WR|IR}}\n{{NFLplayer|98|Dwan Edwards|DE|IR}}\n{{NFLplayer|56|Keith Ellison|d=American football|ILB|IR}}\n{{NFLplayer|83|Lee Evans|d=American football|WR|IR}}\n{{NFLplayer|68|Cordaro Howard|rookie=y|OT|IR}}\n{{NFLplayer|15|Felton Huggins|WR|IR}}\n{{NFLplayer|55|Shawne Merriman|OLB/DE|IR}}\n{{NFLplayer|89|Shawn Nelson|d=American football|TE|NF-Ill.}}\n{{NFLplayer|11|Roscoe Parrish|WR|IR}}\n{{NFLplayer|53|Reggie Torbor|OLB|IR}}\n{{NFLplayer|60|Kraig Urbik|G|IR}}\n|Practice Squad=\n{{NFLplayer|62|Sean Allen|d=American football|rookie=y|C/G}}\n{{NFLplayer|46|Brett Johnson|d=American football|rookie=y|SS}}\n{{NFLplayer|45|Jammie Kirlew|rookie=y|OLB/DE}}\n{{NFLplayer|75|Boo Robinson|rookie=y|NT}}\n{{NFLplayer|45|John Russell|d=American football|rookie=y|OLB|PS/I}}\n{{NFLplayer|66|Jason Watkins|d=American football|OT}}\n{{NFLplayer|16|Bobby Williams|d=American football|rookie=y|WR}}\n{{NFLplayer|47|Trae Williams|CB}}\n{{NFLplayer|--|Rod Windsor|rookie=y|WR}}\n\n}}\n\n==Schedule==\n\n===Preseason===\nThe Bills preseason schedule was announced on March 31, 2010. The second preseason game, against the Indianapolis Colts, was held at the [[Rogers Centre]] in Toronto as part of the [[Bills Toronto Series]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.buffalobills.com/news/article-1/Bills-announce-preseason-game-opponents/62710106-1f9f-47cb-9c48-f0d7c76c4b23 |title=Bills announce preseason game opponents |access-date=April 2, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100402201042/http://www.buffalobills.com/news/article-1/Bills-announce-preseason-game-opponents/62710106-1f9f-47cb-9c48-f0d7c76c4b23 |archive-date=April 2, 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Buffalo Bills|year=2010|border=2}}\"| Week\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Buffalo Bills|year=2010|border=2}}\"| Date\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Buffalo Bills|year=2010|border=2}}\"| Opponent\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Buffalo Bills|year=2010|border=2}}\"| Result\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Buffalo Bills|year=2010|border=2}}\"| Record\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Buffalo Bills|year=2010|border=2}}\"| Game site\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Buffalo Bills|year=2010|border=2}}\"| NFL.com<br>recap\n|- style=\"background:#fcc;\"\n! 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{dow tooltip|August 13, 2010}} || style=\"text-align:center;\"| at [[2010 Washington Redskins season|Washington Redskins]] || style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''L''' 17\u201342 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 0\u20131 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[FedExField]] || style=\"text-align:center;\"| [http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2010081351/2010/PRE1/bills@redskins Recap]\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n! 2\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|  {{dow tooltip|August 19, 2010}} || style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[2010 Indianapolis Colts season|Indianapolis Colts]] || style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''W''' 34\u201321 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\u20131 || style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{flagicon|Canada}}  [[Rogers Centre]]  {{small|([[Toronto]])}} || style=\"text-align:center;\"| [http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2010081952/2010/PRE2/colts@bills Recap]\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n! 3\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|  {{dow tooltip|August 28, 2010}} || style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[2010 Cincinnati Bengals season|Cincinnati Bengals]] || style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''W''' 35\u201320 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2\u20131 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Ralph Wilson Stadium]] || style=\"text-align:center;\"| [http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2010082853/2010/PRE3/bengals@bills Recap]\n|- style=\"background:#fcc;\"\n! 4\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|  {{dow tooltip|September 2, 2010}} || style=\"text-align:center;\"| at [[2010 Detroit Lions season|Detroit Lions]] || style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''L''' 23\u201328 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2\u20132 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Ford Field]] || style=\"text-align:center;\"| [http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2010090251/2010/PRE4/bills@lions Recap]\n|-\n|}\n\n===Regular season===\nFootball statistics site ''[[Football Outsiders]]'' calculates that the Bills had the toughest schedule in the league in 2010, based on strength of opponent,<ref>[http://www.footballoutsiders.com/dvoa-ratings/2011/final-2010-dvoa-ratings Final 2010 DVOA Ratings]</ref> whilst ''[[Pro-Football-Reference.com|Pro Football Reference]]'' argues that the 2010 Bills had the toughest schedule for any NFL team since [[1971 NFL season|1971]], with nine games against opponents 10\u20136 or better.<ref>''Pro Football Reference''; [https://www.pro-football-reference.com/teams/buf/2010.htm 2010 Buffalo Bills]</ref> Apart from their [[AFC East]] division games, the Bills played against the [[AFC North]] and [[NFC North]] according to the conference rotation, and played [[2010 Kansas City Chiefs season|the Chiefs]] and [[2010 Jacksonville Jaguars season|Jaguars]] based on 2009 divisional positions.\n\nThough the Bills were the last team to record their first win in 2010, starting the season with eight consecutive losses, they improved greatly in the second half of the season, with a record of 4\u20134 to finish the year. Nine of the Bills' twelve losses were to teams that qualified for the postseason, including both representatives in [[Super Bowl XLV]] \u2013 Pittsburgh and Green Bay. Six of the twelve losses were by eight points or less. Four Buffalo losses had a margin of three points or less and three losses were in overtime, all to eventual playoff teams (Week 7 at Baltimore, Week 8 at Kansas City and Week 12 vs. Pittsburgh).\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Buffalo Bills|year=2010|border=2}}\"| Week\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Buffalo Bills|year=2010|border=2}}\"| Date\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Buffalo Bills|year=20